    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>On Essex County As Literary Inspiration</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John Debold letter on Debra Galant's September 17 article on literary inspiration from Essex County, NJ, notes that is why he lives in Bloomfield (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As a lifelong resident of Essex County, I enjoyed Debra Galant's well-researched article. As a Bloomfield resident, I especially agreed with her assessment: ''Bloomfield is also a place where . . . suburbanization has not yet bleached all the grit and gumption out of its children.'' I will henceforth add this to the list of reasons I've chosen to raise my two daughters here.</p>
        <p>JOHN DEBOLD  Bloomfield</p>
      </block>
